        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:03PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cypress, or near Jersey Village, moving northwest at 10 mph. Storms
are propagating north along an outflow boundary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tomball, Jersey Village, Pinehurst, northern Addicks Park Ten,
Stagecoach, Willowbrook, and Cypress.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
